e. That is a surprising API-behavior mismatch unless intentional and documented.\\n\\n- **P3 Batched set-add log semantics diverge from existing `set_add`.** Existing `set_add` logs the resulting full set via `encode_set_values_by_metadata_id` ([sets.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/db/sets.rs:181)). The new batch helper logs only the input `members` slice ([lists.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/db/lists.rs:287)), preserving duplicates/order even though storage deduplicates. Any audit/log consumer will see different values for single vs batched set-add.\\n\\nTargeted check run: `cargo test -p git-meta-lib test_apply_edits` passed, with existing dead-code warnings.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>"}]}}}